The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Glaxo posts 30% rise in earnings 

 OUR BUREAU

 April 28: GlaxoSmithKline Consumer Healthcare today posted a 30 per cent increase in its net profit at Rs 34.4 crore for the quarter ended March 31 against Rs 26.3 crore for the corresponding period last year.

 The total revenue grew 24 per cent to Rs 228.9 crore compared with Rs 284.1 crore for the same quarter last fiscal, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 The companys shares closed at Rs 610.9, down 1.48 per cent on the BSE. 

 Cadila profit

 Cadila Healthcare has posted a 40 per cent increase in its net profit at Rs 22.3 crore for the quarter ended March 31 against Rs 15.9 crore in the same period last year.

 Total income for the quarter also jumped 30 per cent at Rs 290.3 crore from Rs 221.7 crore in the same period last year, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 The board has recommended a dividend of Rs 6 on shares of Rs 5 each (120 per cent) for the financial year.

 For the year ended March 31, the companys net profit grew 25 per cent to Rs 164.9 crore from Rs 131.4 crore last year.

 Total income for the year under review rose to Rs 1,321.6 crore against Rs 1,141.9 crore in the previous fiscal.

 The groups net profit stood at Rs 30.6 crore for the quarter ended March 31 compared with Rs 6.4 crore for the same period last year.

 Pantaloon sales up

 Kishore Biyani-promoted Pantaloon Retail India has announced gross sales for the three months ended March 31, 2006 at Rs 5,203.39 crore, a rise of 69 per cent over Rs 3,087.30 crore in the year-ago period.

 The companys net sales for the same period rose 65 per cent from Rs 2,749.57 to Rs 4,553.95 crore a year ago. 

 Pantaloons net sales from operations for the three months ended March 31 stood at Rs 4,553.95 against Rs 2,749.57 crore for the year-ago period. 

 The board has also informed the stock exchange about setting up a property division, comprising 19 malls. 




